Method Summary
 void dontDropBalls()
          Closes the ball cage.
 void dropBalls()
          Opens the ball cage.
 void moveArmDown()
          Sets arm motor to the down speed.If the potentiometer reads a certain value then open the ball cage.
 void moveArmUp()
          Sets arm motor to the up speed.
 void moveToBottomPosition()
          When the BOTTOM_BUTTON is pressed the ball cage will pull into the arm and the arm will go down until the the bottom limit switch is hit.If there are two balls in the processor then the cage will close.
 void moveToMidPosition()
          When the MIDDLE_BUTTON is pressed and the arm is at the MIDDLE_POS nothing will happen.When the MIDDLE_BUTTON is pressed and the arm is above the MIDDLE_POS the arm will go down, when the arm is below the MIDDLE_POS the arm will go up.
 void moveToScoringPosition()
          When the SCORING_BUTTON is pressed and the arm is below the top limit switch, the arm will go up until the potentiometer reads the scoring value.When the SCORING_BUTTON is pressed and the arm is at the top limit switch nothing will happen.
 void run()
          When either the SCORING_BUTTON, the MIDDLE_BUTTON, the BOTTOM_BUTTON, the BALLCLOSE_BUTTON, or the BALLOPEN_BUTTON is the only button pressed, the proper method will be called to move the arm.
 void stopArm()
          Turns off the arm motor.
